<tr></tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2 align=center>1</td>
<td align=center>Tu 31 Aug</td> 
<td align=center>1</td> 
<td colspan=2>
<a href="syllabus.html">Syllabus</a> and goals of the course.
Definition of cognitive psychology: Cognitive psychology explains
mental phenomena primarily in terms of information processing, only
secondarily in terms of neural processing.  All well specified
theories posit particular <em>
<a href="repproc.html">
representations and processes</a></em>.
</td>
<tr>
<td align=center>Th 2 Sept</td> 
<td align=center>2</td> 
<td colspan=2><a href="patternrecog.html">Pattern recognition</a>: 
Perception is
an inference, a construction, from ambiguous sensory information
(even <a href="nunbun.html">perception of cinnamon rolls</a>).
Theories of pattern recognition based on different representations:
templates, 
<a href="featurerep.html">features</a>
 and structures.
</td> 
</tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2 align=center>2</td>
<td align=center>Tu 7 Sept</td> 
<td align=center>2</td> 
<td colspan=2><a href="patternrecog.html">Pattern recognition</a>: Bottom-up
(image driven) and top-down (knowledge driven) context effects.  Use
of context in recognition is usually a very effective way to reduce
ambiguity in interpreting an image.  </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align=center>Th 9 Sept</td> 
<td align=center>2</td> 
<td colspan=2>
The partial-report procedure and visual attention: Iconic memory has
large capacity and fades rapidly, acts as a buffer for directing
attention.  The role of attention in pattern perception: feature
integration. An example of lack of feature integration in unattended
items: <a href="rabbit1.html">a card trick</a>.
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2 align=center>3</td>
<td align=center>Tu 14 Sept</td> 
<td align=center>2,3</td> 
<td>
Visual search paradigm and feature integration theory of attention.
Attention to locations, objects and events.</td>
<td><a href="hw1intro.html">Homework 1 (template model) DUE</a>
 at beginning of class. 
(<a href="hw1results.html">Summary of Data from Homework 1</a>.)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=center>Th 16 Sept</td> 
<td align=center>3</td> 
<td>
Discussion of proposals.
Bottleneck and capacity perspectives on attention.
</td>
<td><a href="relevance.html#proposal">Relevance paper PROPOSAL</a> 1 
DUE at beginning of class.
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2 align=center>4</td>
<td align=center>Tu 21 Sept <sup><strong>*</strong></sup></td> 
<td align=center>3</td> 
<td>Bottleneck and capacity perspectives on attention 
(cont.).  
Attention in bus drivers and fighter pilots.
<a href="part1conclusion.html">Conclusion to Part I.</a>
</td>
<td><a href="relevance.html#structure">Relevance PAPER</a> 1 DUE at 
beginning of class.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=center>Th 23 Sept</td> 
